cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CL 

This paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms and their application in real-world scenarios such as dialogue systems, pharmaceutical tests, and crop management. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. The paper also discusses the use of human supervision in data collection, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of reinforcement learning algorithms in control tasks and the focus on safe policy improvement make cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper's focus on dialogue systems suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper's theoretical grounding and formal guarantees suggest a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control).
